<HEAD>FSX Settlement Avoided Rift, Says New U.S. Envoy</HEAD>
<BYLINE>By GENE KRAMER</BYLINE>
<BYLINE>Associated Press Writer</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 The <LOCATION> United </LOCATION> <LOCATION> States </LOCATION> averted a potentially serious rift in U.S.-Japanese relations by going ahead with the controversial agreement for the two countries to develop jointly a new jet fighter for <LOCATION> Japan </LOCATION>, the new American ambassador to <LOCATION> Tokyo </LOCATION> said Monday. Ambassador <PERSON> Michael </PERSON> <PERSON> Armacost </PERSON> told reporters that despite persistent, strong objections to the project on <LOCATION> Capitol </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Hill </LOCATION>, `` I'm confident it will meet with the acquiescence of our <ORGANIZATION> Congress </ORGANIZATION>. President <PERSON> Bush </PERSON> announced Friday that the <LOCATION> United </LOCATION> <LOCATION> States </LOCATION> intends to proceed with the FSX fighter program because it is `` in the strategic and commercial interests of the <LOCATION> United </LOCATION> <LOCATION> States </LOCATION>.'' After taking office in January, <PERSON> Bush </PERSON> ordered a review of the $ 7 billion project negotiated under his predecessor, <PERSON> Ronald </PERSON> <PERSON> Reagan </PERSON>. Critics in <ORGANIZATION> Congress </ORGANIZATION> and the <ORGANIZATION> Commerce </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Department </ORGANIZATION> have said it amounts to a giveaway of <LOCATION> U.S. </LOCATION> high technology and have said <LOCATION> Japan </LOCATION> should make an `` off-the-shelf'' aircraft purchase, as do other nations that are <LOCATION> U.S. </LOCATION> customers. <PERSON> Armacost </PERSON> brought up the negative side of scrapping the agreement in an appearance at the <LOCATION> Washington </LOCATION> Foreign Press Center on the eve of his departure for <LOCATION> Japan </LOCATION>, where he is due next week. Proceeding with the FSX project `` is important from our standpoint because of what it avoided, namely -LRB- <LOCATION> America </LOCATION> and <LOCATION> Japan </LOCATION> -RRB- going down separate tracks,'' he said. `` It avoids what could have been an important breach in our relationship if this deal had gone awry.'' The FSX agreement `` is a good arrangement for both our governments. We have had coproduction in past, but major codevelopment is in a sense the first'' such arrangement with <LOCATION> Japan </LOCATION>, said <PERSON> Armacost </PERSON>, a former undersecretary of state for political affairs. `` I hope this will be a model of the flow of two-way technology which is quite appropriate to a more mature relationship between our countries in this field,'' the ambassador said. The White House said Monday that, with <LOCATION> Japan </LOCATION>, <PERSON> Bush </PERSON> `` has been very tough in demanding equity for the <LOCATION> United </LOCATION> <LOCATION> States </LOCATION> in terms of its commercial interests,'' and he `` was successful in getting everything he asked for.'' Friday's announcement said <LOCATION> U.S. </LOCATION> companies would be guaranteed about 40 percent of the production work on the planned 130 new fighters while certain computer codes from the <LOCATION> U.S. </LOCATION> F-16 jet, which provides the model for the FSX, would be withheld.
