<HEAD>Wal-Mart Restocks Listerine</HEAD>
<BYLINE>By SCOTT CHARTON</BYLINE>
<BYLINE>Associated Press Writer</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>LITTLE ROCK, Ark. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 <ORGANIZATION> Wal-Mart </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Stores </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Inc. </ORGANIZATION> ordered its outlets in 26 states Monday to restock Listerine pulled from shelves over the weekend after a woman said the mouthwash burned her mouth. Officials at <ORGANIZATION> Wal-Mart </ORGANIZATION> headquarters in <LOCATION> Bentonville </LOCATION> began notifying managers of the chain's 1,279 stores to return thousands of bottles of the mouthwash to shelves after extensive testing by manufacturer <ORGANIZATION> Warner-Lambert </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Co. </ORGANIZATION>. <ORGANIZATION> Warner-Lambert </ORGANIZATION> rushed the unused portion of the suspect bottle through analysis Sunday night at its <LOCATION> New </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Jersey </LOCATION> laboratory, and conducted more tests early Monday The tests found only normal product ingredients. The mouthwash was removed from <ORGANIZATION> Wal-Mart </ORGANIZATION> shelves Saturday. `` We believed from the beginning this was an isolated incident. However, we chose not to take any chances,'' said <PERSON> Don </PERSON> <PERSON> Fields </PERSON>, <ORGANIZATION> Wal-Mart </ORGANIZATION>'s executive vice president for merchandising. `` The safety and well-being of our customers come first.'' Listerine was expected to be back on the shelves of all <ORGANIZATION> Wal-Mart </ORGANIZATION> stores by Monday night, said company spokesman <PERSON> Don </PERSON> <PERSON> Shinkle </PERSON>. <ORGANIZATION> Wal-Mart </ORGANIZATION> officials have not determined how much removing the mouthwash had cost the company, <PERSON> Shinkle </PERSON> said. He said no one was second-guessing the decision to do so. `` We stand by our decision and feel it was the thing to do,'' <PERSON> Shinkle </PERSON> said. `` Our customers would more than agree with that.'' The woman, whom company officials have declined to identify, complained Saturday that her mouth was red and irritated after using Listerine she bought at a <ORGANIZATION> Wal-Mart </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Store </ORGANIZATION> in <ORGANIZATION> Rogers </ORGANIZATION>, Ark. She sought treatment from a dentist and `` is fine,'' <PERSON> Shinkle </PERSON> said. <PERSON> Barry </PERSON> <PERSON> S. </PERSON> <PERSON> Cohen </PERSON>, a spokesman for <ORGANIZATION> Warner-Lambert </ORGANIZATION> in <LOCATION> Morris </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Plains </LOCATION>, <LOCATION> N.J. </LOCATION>, said no other problems had been reported with Listerine, which is made at a plant in <LOCATION> Lititz </LOCATION>, <LOCATION> Pa. </LOCATION> `` It's a 125-year-old product. It's shipped around the country. If there's some problem with the product we would have received other calls, but we have n't,'' <PERSON> Cohen </PERSON> said. No ingredient in Listerine would cause burns, even when mixed in excessive amounts, <PERSON> Cohen </PERSON> said. The mouthwash is marketed as an antiseptic, however, and can cause an astringent, tingly sensation. <ORGANIZATION> Wal-Mart </ORGANIZATION> has stores in <LOCATION> Alabama </LOCATION>, <LOCATION> Arizona </LOCATION>, <LOCATION> Arkansas </LOCATION>, <LOCATION> Colorado </LOCATION>, <LOCATION> Florida </LOCATION>, <LOCATION> Georgia </LOCATION>, <LOCATION> Illinois </LOCATION>, <LOCATION> Indiana </LOCATION>, <LOCATION> Iowa </LOCATION>, <LOCATION> Kansas </LOCATION>, <LOCATION> Kentucky </LOCATION>, <LOCATION> Louisiana </LOCATION>, <LOCATION> Minnesota </LOCATION>, <LOCATION> Mississippi </LOCATION>, <LOCATION> Missouri </LOCATION>, <LOCATION> Nebraska </LOCATION>, <LOCATION> New </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Mexico </LOCATION>, <LOCATION> North </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Carolina </LOCATION>, <LOCATION> Ohio </LOCATION>, <LOCATION> Oklahoma </LOCATION>, <LOCATION> South </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Carolina </LOCATION>, <LOCATION> Tennessee </LOCATION>, <LOCATION> Texas </LOCATION>, <LOCATION> Virginia </LOCATION>, <LOCATION> West </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Virginia </LOCATION> and <LOCATION> Wisconsin </LOCAT