 `` Running on Empty'' -LRB- <ORGANIZATION> Warner </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Home </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Video </ORGANIZATION>. VHS-Beta, $ 89.95. Rated PG-13 -RRB- What ever happened to all those Weather people from the late 1960s and early'70s, all those revolutionaries who bombed government buildings and corporations with government contracts? All those radicals who may have killed innocents in the name of freedom and liberty? They went underground. But underground is as ordinary as the family next door. `` Running on Empty'' looks at such a family, who have been wanted by the <ORGANIZATION> FBI </ORGANIZATION> for their part in a bombing in which a security guard was accidently killed. The young couple made one mistake, though. Not only did they take their young son, <PERSON> Danny </PERSON>, with them as they fled, they also conceived another child while underground, <PERSON> Harry </PERSON>. Cut to the'80s. <PERSON> Danny </PERSON> -LRB- <LOCATION> River </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Phoenix </LOCATION> -RRB- is a 17-year-old musical prodigy. What to do. If he stays with his parents, as they want him to, he must give up all ambitions in music and indeed give up his own destiny. If he leaves them and heads for the <ORGANIZATION> Juilliard </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> School </ORGANIZATION>, he will never be able to see them again unless they surrender to authorities. There is much tenderness in this movie, especially from <PERSON> Christine </PERSON> <PERSON> Lahti </PERSON> as the mother. <PERSON> Judd </PERSON> <PERSON> Hirsch </PERSON>'s father seems somewhat outmoded in his'60s politics and'60s perceptions. He's also a little selfish. He's not a very likeable man until the end, and resolution of the movie. <PERSON> Naomi </PERSON> <PERSON> Foner </PERSON> has a tight and gripping screenplay, and <PERSON> Sidney </PERSON> <PERSON> Lumet </PERSON>'s direction is powerful. It's a nice movie for the entire family because `` Running on Empty'' is ultimat