 Billionaire hotelier <PERSON> Jay </PERSON> <PERSON> Pritzker </PERSON> and other suitors formally have submitted bids for strikebound <ORGANIZATION> Eastern </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Airlines </ORGANIZATION>, but the carrier remained locked on its planned course of cutting operations and selling $ 1.8 billion in assets. While confirming that the airline had received an offer from <PERSON> Pritzker </PERSON>, <ORGANIZATION> Eastern </ORGANIZATION> spokesman <PERSON> Robin </PERSON> <PERSON> Matell </PERSON> insisted `` there are still no bona fide offers to buy Eastern.'' Eastern's managers recently detailed plans to operate at one-third the airline's pre-strike size and raise cash by selling assets, including planes, airport gates and landing slots at unspecified locations.
