<TEXT>
 The stock market showed little change in slackened trading Friday, bogging down after Thursday's rally to new post-crash highs. The Dow Jones average of 30 industrials slipped .19 to 2,418.80. The dollar rose sharply against all major currencies except the Canadian dollar. Gold prices took a tumble. Bond prices fell. Precious metals futures dropped sharply; wheat futures rose while corn and soybean prices fell; cattle prices rallied but hog prices retreated; and energy prices were mixed.
