<FILEID>AP-NR-05-01-89 1120EST</FILEID>
<FIRST>u f PM-WallStreet11am     05-01 0280</FIRST>
<SECOND>PM-Wall Street 11am,0295</SECOND>
<DATELINE>NEW YORK (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 The stock market suffered a broad setback today, faced with evidence of persistent strength in the economy. The Dow Jones average of 30 industrials fell 18.14 points to 2,400.66 by 11 a.m. on Wall Street. Losers outnumbered gainers by more than 8 to 3 in nationwide trading of <ORGANIZATION> New </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> York </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Stock </ORGANIZATION> Exchange-listed issues, with 333 up, 896 down and 475 unchanged. Volume on the <ORGANIZATION> Big </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Board </ORGANIZATION> came to 43.57 million shares at midmorning. Analysts said investors were caught off guard by signs of a pickup in business activity, as reported by the <ORGANIZATION> National </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Association </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> of </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Purchasing </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Management </ORGANIZATION>. The trade group said the pace of business tracked by its members stepped up in April to a brisk pace. That came as unwelcome news to stock and bond traders who had been banking on a continued slowing in the economy, in keeping with the <ORGANIZATION> Federal </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Reserve </ORGANIZATION>'s aim of restraining inflation. The news sent interest rates higher in the credit markets. Prices of long-term government bonds, which move in the opposite direction from interest rates, fell about $ 5 for each $ 1,000 in face value. Among the blue chips, <ORGANIZATION> International </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Business </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Machines </ORGANIZATION> dropped 1 to 113 -LRB-; <ORGANIZATION> Eastman </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Kodak </ORGANIZATION> | to 47 -RRB-; <ORGANIZATION> Ford </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Motor </ORGANIZATION> \ to 47 -LCB-, and <ORGANIZATION> American </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Telephone </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> & </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> amp </ORGANIZATION>; <ORGANIZATION> Telegraph </ORGANIZATION> -RRB- to 34 -LCB