<DATELINE>NEW YORK (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 <ORGANIZATION> Federal </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Home </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Loan </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Bank </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Board </ORGANIZATION> Chairman <PERSON> M. </PERSON> <PERSON> Danny </PERSON> <PERSON> Wall </PERSON> said Monday that reports of the savings and loan industry's death have been greatly exaggerated `` Do n't get caught up that the industry is some sort of a dinosaur,'' he told the <ORGANIZATION> Society </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> of </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> American </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Business </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Editors </ORGANIZATION> and Writers. `` The industry is doing well within the healthy sector.'' Speaking in typical optimistic fashion, <PERSON> Wall </PERSON> said that 88 percent of the nation's 3,000 <ORGANIZATION> S </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> & </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> amp </ORGANIZATION>; Ls, representing 92 percent of the industy's assets, are considered solvent, and <ORGANIZATION> Congress </ORGANIZATION> is working to dispose of the rest. Troubled thrifts accounted for the bulk of the $ 12.1 billion in industrywide losses in 1988, with <LOCATION> Texas </LOCATION> institutions again emerging as the biggest losers. `` The future of the industry is being made ever clear ... as legislative discussion continues,'' <PERSON> Wall </PERSON> said. `` <ORGANIZATION> Congress </ORGANIZATION> continues to be supportive of the thrift industry and in its purpose.'' He said that he expected a thrift bailout bill to pass through <ORGANIZATION> Congress </ORGANIZATION> by mid-June. Last week, the <ORGANIZATION> Senate </ORGANIZATION> overwhelmingly approved a record $ 157 billion bailout and reform bill for the <ORGANIZATION> S </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> & </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> amp </ORGANIZATION>; L industry after toughening provisions that would require S & amp; L owners to put more of their own money at risk to stay in business. <ORGANIZATION> Similar </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> S </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> & </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> amp </ORGANIZATION>; L legislation is pending in the House.
