oil flow through the <LOCATION> Alaska </LOCATION> pipeline over a 12-day period after the March 24 spill. `` About 3.2 million barrels net to <ORGANIZATION> Arco </ORGANIZATION> was not delivered,'' said <PERSON> Albert </PERSON> <PERSON> Greenstein </PERSON>. `` So when you look at reduced deliveries to <ORGANIZATION> Arco </ORGANIZATION> and reduced production _ we had to reduce production in one of our refineries _ the overall after-tax loss was $ 10 million. Most of that relates to loss of delivered crude.''
