<HEAD>Congressman Wants Bush to Block Takeover</HEAD>
<BYLINE>By JANE E. ALLEN</BYLINE>
<BYLINE>Associated Press Writer</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 Rep. <PERSON> James </PERSON> <PERSON> J. </PERSON> <PERSON> Florio </PERSON>, <LOCATION> D-N.J. </LOCATION>, suggested Monday that President <PERSON> George </PERSON> <PERSON> Bush </PERSON> safeguard national security by blocking the proposed acquisition of American mineral interests by a South African-linked company, but government lawyers said the president lacks the authority to intervene. `` By allowing this takeover we are undercutting the effectiveness of our country's anti-apartheid policy,'' <PERSON> Florio </PERSON> wrote in a letter requesting that <PERSON> Bush </PERSON> act under a provision of the 1988 trade bill that the <LOCATION> New </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Jersey </LOCATION> congressman co-authored with Sen. <PERSON> J. </PERSON> <PERSON> James </PERSON> <PERSON> Exon </PERSON>, D-Neb. <PERSON> Florio </PERSON> asked that <PERSON> Bush </PERSON> investigate a $ 6 billion takeover offer made by <ORGANIZATION> Minorco </ORGANIZATION>, a Luxembourg-based holding company controlled by South African interests. <ORGANIZATION> Minorco </ORGANIZATION> wants to acquire <ORGANIZATION> Consolidated </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Gold </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Fields </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> PLC </ORGANIZATION>, a London-based mining company whose American holdings include <ORGANIZATION> Associated </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Minerals </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> USA </ORGANIZATION> and the <ORGANIZATION> Newmont </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Mining </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Co. </ORGANIZATION> _ producers of gold, rutile, zircon, monazite, and other strategic minerals with military and nuclear applications. <PERSON> Florio </PERSON> said he's concerned the deal could increase <LOCATION> South </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Africa </LOCATION>'s control over production of the minerals. `` I believe this takeover raises important security questions for the <LOCATION> U.S. </LOCATION>, which may not have been adequately considered previously, when this matter was under review by the inter-agency <ORGANIZATION> Committee </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> on </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Foreign </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Investment </ORGANIZATION> in the <LOCATION> United </LOCATION> <LOCATION> States </LOCATION>,'' said <PERSON> Florio </PERSON>, chairman of the subcommittee on commerce, consumer protection and competitiveness. However, <PERSON> Steve </PERSON> <PERSON> Canner </PERSON>, staff chairman of the inter-agency committee, said the panel had fully reviewed the merger and decided against proceeding with an investigation. `` If the committee decides not to go forward, that's it,'' he said. According to documents supplied by the <ORGANIZATION> Treasury </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Department </ORGANIZATION>, government attorneys reviewed the deal's potential impact on strategic metals as well as anti-apartheid laws before concluding `` the transaction posed no threat to the <LOCATION> U.S. </LOCATION> national security.'' Government attorneys said Monday that based on the legislative history that accompanied the trade bill and the executive order implementing the bill, once the 30-day review period ended without a decision to proceed to an investigation, action under Exon-Florio had concluded and the president had no authority to resurrect the issue. <ORGANIZATION> Minorco </ORGANIZATION>, which is 60 percent owned by <ORGANIZATION> Anglo </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> American </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Corp. </ORGANIZATION> of <LOCATION> South </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Africa </LOCATION> and <ORGANIZATION> De </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Beers </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Consolidated </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Mines </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Ltd. </ORGANIZATION>, is the largest producer of gold in the non-communist world. Gold Fields is the world's second-largest gold concern.
